==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photograph
<hw>Pho"to*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>A picture or
likeness obtained by photography.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photograph</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Photograph
<hw>Pho"to*graph</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Photographed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Photographing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To take a
picture or likeness of by means of photography; <as>as, to
<ex>photograph</ex> a view; to <ex>photograph</ex> a
group.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He makes his pen drawing on white paper, and they are afterwards
<qex>photographed</qex> on wood.</q> <rj><qau>Hamerton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>Also used figuratively.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is <qex>photographed</qex> on my mind.</q> <rj><qau>Lady D.
Hardy.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photograph</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Photograph
<hw>Pho"to*graph</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To practice photography; to
take photographs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photographer</ent>⟦br⟧
